01:05:44,027 --> 01:05:47,614
How can we do that
to people?

1013
01:05:49,700 --> 01:05:52,995
And you have to get
her off that stuff.

1014
01:05:53,036 --> 01:05:55,497
It's inhuman.

1015
01:05:58,000 --> 01:06:00,460
How long has she been
in prison now?

1016
01:06:00,502 --> 01:06:02,504
14 years.

1017
01:06:02,546 --> 01:06:05,007
And the average term
served by a life prisoner?

1018
01:06:05,048 --> 01:06:06,758
12 years.

1019
01:06:08,260 --> 01:06:11,597
And still, she's been given
no prospect of parole.

1020
01:06:11,638 --> 01:06:13,724
No.

1021
01:06:13,765 --> 01:06:17,644
You said the trial judge
made a distinction

1022
01:06:17,686 --> 01:06:19,813
between her case
and Ian Brady's.

1023
01:06:19,855 --> 01:06:23,317
I quote,
"Though I believe

1024
01:06:23,358 --> 01:06:25,360
Brady is wicked
beyond belief,

1025
01:06:25,402 --> 01:06:28,697
I cannot feel the same
is necessarily true of Hindley

1026
01:06:28,739 --> 01:06:30,866
when she is removed
from his influence."

1027
01:06:30,908 --> 01:06:34,036
End of quote.

1028
01:06:34,077 --> 01:06:35,954
Really?

1029
01:06:41,460 --> 01:06:43,420
...who between the wars,

1030
01:06:43,462 --> 01:06:45,756
converted more people
to Catholicism...

1031
01:06:45,797 --> 01:06:47,549
How's the Queen Mother
coming along?

1032
01:06:47,591 --> 01:06:50,302
Rather slowly,
I'm afraid.

1033
01:06:50,344 --> 01:06:53,847
I've got bogged down
researching something else.

1034
01:06:53,889 --> 01:06:55,849
Can you say what?

1035
01:06:55,891 --> 01:06:59,144
Myra Hindley.

1036
01:06:59,186 --> 01:07:01,146
What? Why?

1037
01:07:01,188 --> 01:07:02,731
...what a meddler.

1038
01:07:02,773 --> 01:07:05,359
It seemed to me that
for years I have been

1039
01:07:05,400 --> 01:07:08,362
merrily attacking your father
for supporting her

1040
01:07:08,403 --> 01:07:11,657
without having the slightest idea
of what I was talking about.

1041
01:07:11,698 --> 01:07:14,284
- And there you go.
- And?

1042
01:07:14,326 --> 01:07:18,080
And I must say
my eyes have been opened rather.

1043
01:07:18,121 --> 01:07:21,250
How much do you
know about

1044
01:07:21,291 --> 01:07:23,961
the nature
of sadomasochistic relationships?

1045
01:07:24,002 --> 01:07:26,255
Mercifully, very little.

1046
01:07:26,255 --> 01:07:29,466
Isn't it an accepted
psychological fact

1047
01:07:29,508 --> 01:07:32,594
that daughters seek
in their husbands or lovers

1048
01:07:32,636 --> 01:07:35,430
someone who mirrors
their own father?

1049
01:07:35,472 --> 01:07:37,516
One of the papers claimed

1050
01:07:37,558 --> 01:07:40,602
that Myra Hindley was
abused by her father.

1051
01:07:40,644 --> 01:07:42,855
So it makes perfect sense

1052
01:07:42,896 --> 01:07:45,899
that she would then repeat
the pattern with Ian Brady,

1053
01:07:45,941 --> 01:07:49,236
who subjected her
to the most appalling cruelty,

1054
01:07:49,278 --> 01:07:51,572
beating her,
raping her,

1055
01:07:51,613 --> 01:07:53,699
threatening
to take her life.

1056
01:07:53,740 --> 01:07:57,828
I see. So it's not her fault
she procured children for him?

1057
01:07:57,870 --> 01:08:00,122
She made repeated attempts
to free herself

1058
01:08:00,122 --> 01:08:02,124
of him,
running away to London.

1059
01:08:02,124 --> 01:08:04,835
But every time
came back... funny that.

1060
01:08:04,877 --> 01:08:08,380
Isn't that the nature
of obsession?

1061
01:08:08,422 --> 01:08:12,926
The fear of losing Brady
was greater than anything else.

1062
01:08:12,968 --> 01:08:14,678
And you got all
this from?

1063
01:08:14,720 --> 01:08:16,263
The public records' office,

1064
01:08:16,305 --> 01:08:18,515
where I read the original
trial transcripts,

1065
01:08:18,557 --> 01:08:21,560
and I spoke to Dorothy Wing,
her former governor at Holloway.

1066
01:08:21,602 --> 01:08:24,313
But...

1067
01:08:24,313 --> 01:08:28,525
ironically, the thing that finally
persuaded me to offer her my help

1068
01:08:28,567 --> 01:08:32,529
was the very same thing
that had so made me

1069
01:08:32,571 --> 01:08:34,364
hate her
in the first place:

1070
01:08:34,406 --> 01:08:36,742
the fact that she
is a woman.

1071
01:08:36,783 --> 01:08:38,452
Did you know

1072
01:08:38,493 --> 01:08:41,163
there have been half a dozen
similar child murders?

1073
01:08:41,205 --> 01:08:44,166
The reason none of us
has heard about them

1074
01:08:44,208 --> 01:08:46,877
is because the killers
in each case were men.

1075
01:08:46,919 --> 01:08:50,047
And men being sadistic
violent killers

1076
01:08:50,088 --> 01:08:51,840
isn't a story.

1077
01:08:51,882 --> 01:08:53,967
Incidentally,
in each case

1078
01:08:54,009 --> 01:08:56,803
the men have also
been paroled.

1079
01:08:56,845 --> 01:09:00,265
Note the reason
Myra Hindley is still in jail

1080
01:09:00,307 --> 01:09:02,726
and has never been
considered for parole

1081
01:09:02,768 --> 01:09:04,603
is because she
is a woman.

1082
01:09:04,645 --> 01:09:06,605
And for that reason,

1083
01:09:06,647 --> 01:09:08,982
she will always have
my understanding,

1084
01:09:09,024 --> 01:09:12,402
if not my sympathy.

1085
01:09:12,444 --> 01:09:16,156
So when did you go
to the public records office?

1086
01:09:16,198 --> 01:09:20,035
When I said I was
going to the Bodleian.

1087
01:09:20,077 --> 01:09:23,205
And Governor Wing,
when did you visit her?

1088
01:09:23,247 --> 01:09:27,251
When I said
I was having lunch with my agent.

1089
01:09:27,292 --> 01:09:31,839
So now I must add mendacity
to your many virtues.

1090
01:09:34,675 --> 01:09:37,553
And you'd have me
continue my campaign?

1091
01:09:38,679 --> 01:09:40,556
Yes...

1092
01:09:40,597 --> 01:09:44,059
and not rest
until she gets paroled.

1093
01:09:44,059 --> 01:09:46,812
Have you spoken
to Willie about it?

1094
01:09:46,854 --> 01:09:50,858
Whitelaw?
No, not one to one, no.

1095
01:09:50,899 --> 01:09:53,443
Then I suggest you do that.

1096
01:09:55,404 --> 01:09:58,323
What a very good idea.

1097
01:09:59,575 --> 01:10:01,410
I don't think
I've ever loved you

1098
01:10:01,410 --> 01:10:03,245
quite so completely
as I do now.

1099
01:10:04,913 --> 01:10:07,958
- A new high?
- Off the charts.

1100
01:10:08,000 --> 01:10:10,752
Top of the pops.

1101
01:10:10,794 --> 01:10:12,629
Get into bed, woman!

1102
01:10:12,671 --> 01:10:15,299
I've got to get
my dressing gown off.

1103
01:10:15,340 --> 01:10:17,301
I've got to take
my shoes off.

1104
01:10:19,136 --> 01:10:21,221
The Home Secretary
will see you now.

1105
01:10:21,263 --> 01:10:23,182
Thank you
so much.

1106
01:10:28,103 --> 01:10:31,190
- Frank, good to see you.
- My dear fellow.

1107
01:10:31,231 --> 01:10:33,984
- How good of you to see me.
- Not at all.

1108
01:10:34,026 --> 01:10:35,485
- Come on in.
- Thank you.

1109
01:10:35,527 --> 01:10:38,447
- Sherry?
- You know me too well.

1110
01:10:38,447 --> 01:10:40,574
She's served
almost 15 years, Willie.

1111
01:10:40,616 --> 01:10:43,785
It's a scandal she hasn't
been considered for parole.

1112
01:10:43,827 --> 01:10:46,121
I know. But as
Home Secretary,

1113
01:10:46,121 --> 01:10:49,499
I have to make sure
that public confidence

1114
01:10:49,541 --> 01:10:52,878
in the system
is not undermined.

1115
01:10:52,920 --> 01:10:56,006
If you wish to protect
the integrity of the system,

1116
01:10:56,048 --> 01:10:58,300
I suggest you stop
allowing it to be ruled

1117
01:10:58,342 --> 01:11:00,844
- according to the will of the mob.
- Frank, look...

1118
01:11:00,886 --> 01:11:04,640
At least allow her to be interviewed
by a local parole board.

1119
01:11:04,681 --> 01:11:07,518
For me?
What harm could that do?

1120
01:11:07,559 --> 01:11:11,563
Couldn't she be moved somewhere better?
Durham is insufferable.

1121
01:11:11,605 --> 01:11:14,066
I'll see what I can do.

1122
01:11:14,107 --> 01:11:16,318
If anyone deserves
to be in...

1123
01:11:16,360 --> 01:11:18,195
Frank!

1124
01:11:20,531 --> 01:11:24,326
You really are a most tenacious
campaigner, you know?

1125
01:11:24,326 --> 01:11:26,036
It's an admirable trait.

1126
01:11:27,996 --> 01:11:32,209
And you always pick
the most difficult causes.

1127
01:11:32,251 --> 01:11:36,380
Maybe you should take
a back seat for a while.

1128
01:11:36,421 --> 01:11:39,842
God knows you deserve it.

1129
01:11:39,842 --> 01:11:42,344
I can't, Willie.
You know what they say:

1130
01:11:42,386 --> 01:11:45,681
"Only dead fish swim
with the stream."

1131
01:11:45,722 --> 01:11:48,809
Thank you very much.

1132
01:11:48,851 --> 01:11:50,644
Thank you.

1133
01:11:50,686 --> 01:11:53,814
Goodbye.

1134
01:11:53,856 --> 01:11:55,440
There's good news.

1135
01:11:55,482 --> 01:11:58,902
Willie has agreed for Myra
to be seen by the local parole board.

1136
01:11:58,944 --> 01:12:00,946
And she's going to be
moved from Durham.

1137
01:12:00,988 --> 01:12:02,698
Oh, Frank,
that's wonderful.

1138
01:12:02,739 --> 01:12:04,700
Imagine, if they
find in her favor,

1139
01:12:04,700 --> 01:12:06,952
and the National Board agrees,
that would put

1140
01:12:06,994 --> 01:12:08,996
enormous pressure
on the Home Secretary.

1141
01:12:09,037 --> 01:12:12,457
Then the only thing that will stand
in our way will be public opinion.

1142
01:12:12,499 --> 01:12:15,002
So we must keep a lid on this,
because if the press get

1143
01:12:15,043 --> 01:12:17,629
even the merest hint of it,
we'll be scuppered.

1144
01:12:30,767 --> 01:12:33,562
Fred Harrison?

1145
01:12:33,562 --> 01:12:36,106
Top local reporter.

1146
01:12:43,405 --> 01:12:46,074
Come on, man, smile.

1147
01:12:51,747 --> 01:12:55,125
This is your lucky day.

1148
01:12:55,167 --> 01:12:57,544
You are about to get a story

1149
01:12:57,586 --> 01:13:01,673
on the front page
of every paper in the country.

1150
01:13:07,888 --> 01:13:10,682
Word has reached me

1151
01:13:10,724 --> 01:13:14,353
that Myra Hindley is
being considered for parole.

1152
01:13:14,394 --> 01:13:17,022
I wasn't aware of that.

1153
01:13:17,064 --> 01:13:20,192
No, friend, that's what
makes it an exclusive.

1154
01:13:22,194 --> 01:13:24,696
Turn your tape recorder on,
there's a good lad.

1155
01:13:38,544 --> 01:13:40,587
Morning, Lord Longford.

1156
01:13:40,629 --> 01:13:42,297
Good morning.

1157
01:13:42,339 --> 01:13:44,591
You certainly are
in high spirits today.

1158
01:13:44,633 --> 01:13:47,928
Yes, we are. A bit of a break,
so I believe, for Ms. Hindley.

1159
01:13:47,970 --> 01:13:49,763
Yeah, don't worry.

1160
01:13:49,805 --> 01:13:52,057
Just goes to show,
if you keep persisting

1161
01:13:52,099 --> 01:13:54,351
and persisting...

1162
01:13:54,393 --> 01:13:56,854
Hello, Myra. This is the nightie
you wanted.

1163
01:13:56,895 --> 01:13:58,397
I couldn't remember
what color you asked for.

1164
01:13:58,438 --> 01:14:00,148
That's great, thanks.

1165
01:14:00,148 --> 01:14:02,067
- Now to business.
- Frank...

1166
01:14:02,109 --> 01:14:04,528
I have a friend on the local
parole board

1167
01:14:04,570 --> 01:14:07,698
who tells me that your application
will be considered next month.

1168
01:14:07,739 --> 01:14:10,158
If that goes well,
all things being equal,

1169
01:14:10,158 --> 01:14:13,662
- the national...
- Frank, enough.

1170
01:14:17,583 --> 01:14:19,334
The police have
been to see me.

1171
01:14:22,045 --> 01:14:25,382
Brady's talked to the press
about the other bodies.

1172
01:14:25,424 --> 01:14:27,593
What do you mean,
what other bodies?

1173
01:14:27,634 --> 01:14:31,138
Pauline Reade
and the Bennett boy.

1174
01:14:33,432 --> 01:14:35,434
He hasn't given them
any details yet...

1175
01:14:35,475 --> 01:14:38,729
but he says he knows
where they're buried.

1176
01:14:38,770 --> 01:14:41,690
Before he grabs
the initiative,

1177
01:14:41,690 --> 01:14:45,736
I've decided to come clean
and tell them everything I know.

1178
01:14:47,696 --> 01:14:51,033
But you know nothing about other bodies.
You told me as much yourself.

1179
01:14:54,286 --> 01:14:57,206
What are you saying?

1180
01:14:57,206 --> 01:15:00,209
I'm saying...

1181
01:15:00,209 --> 01:15:03,587
that I'm going to give a full confession
to all five murders.

1182
01:15:06,215 --> 01:15:10,636
Dear God.

1183
01:15:10,677 --> 01:15:12,846
I asked you specifically

1184
01:15:12,888 --> 01:15:16,934
if there was anything
you hadn't told me.

1185
01:15:16,975 --> 01:15:19,520
I've staked my name on this,
my reputation.

1186
01:15:19,561 --> 01:15:20,729
I know.

1187
01:15:20,771 --> 01:15:22,940
And I would
understand perfectly

1188
01:15:22,981 --> 01:15:24,775
if you never wanted
to see me again.

1189
01:15:27,611 --> 01:15:30,739
It's what my new solicitor's
suggested anyway.

1190
01:15:30,781 --> 01:15:33,075
Your new solicitor?

1191
01:15:33,116 --> 01:15:36,495
He feels... and if I'm honest,
I have to agree with him...

1192
01:15:36,537 --> 01:15:41,416
the campaign that you've
conducted on my behalf

1193
01:15:41,458 --> 01:15:43,460
has hurt me
more than helped me,

1194
01:15:43,502 --> 01:15:45,921
and that we should
make this our last meeting.

1195
01:15:48,340 --> 01:15:52,261
I see.

1196
01:15:52,261 --> 01:15:55,264
If that's what he feels,

1197
01:15:55,264 --> 01:15:57,850
and you feel.

1198
01:16:09,528 --> 01:16:11,446
Goodbye, Frank.

1199
01:17:12,633 --> 01:17:14,551
An hour after first light,

1200
01:17:14,593 --> 01:17:17,888
a police helicopter carrying
Myra Hindley and an armed bodyguard,

1201
01:17:17,930 --> 01:17:20,098
landed on the A635...

1202
01:17:20,140 --> 01:17:22,100
the road used
by Hindley and Brady

1203
01:17:22,142 --> 01:17:25,604
when they were carrying the bodies
of their victims up to the moors.

1204
01:17:25,646 --> 01:17:27,940
A small group including
Myra Hindley

1205
01:17:27,981 --> 01:17:30,234
then inspected
the peat slopes.

1206
01:17:32,069 --> 01:17:34,071
Myra, we do know
it's been a long time,

1207
01:17:34,112 --> 01:17:35,906
but you know,
are we in the right spot?

1208
01:17:35,948 --> 01:17:38,742
Myra, we need to know
if this is the spot.

1209
01:17:38,784 --> 01:17:40,244
Can you be sure, Myra?

1210
01:17:40,285 --> 01:17:42,746
Have a look around.
Where in relation to the group?

1211
01:17:47,793 --> 01:17:50,045
- I recognize the rocks behind you.
- You certain?

1212
01:17:50,087 --> 01:17:52,005
Yes yes, I'm certain.

1213
01:17:52,047 --> 01:17:54,883
Hindley led the police
to areas she and Brady

1214
01:17:54,925 --> 01:17:57,261
visited more than
20 years ago.

1215
01:17:57,302 --> 01:17:59,263
In a pub two miles away:

1216
01:17:59,304 --> 01:18:01,223
Pat Kilbride,
whose son John was murdered

1217
01:18:01,265 --> 01:18:03,183
21 years ago.

1218
01:18:03,225 --> 01:18:06,103
He'd come armed with a knife,
but was stopped at a roadblock.

1219
01:18:06,144 --> 01:18:08,939
Just want to say...
this here,

1220
01:18:08,981 --> 01:18:11,358
I've come prepared
to kill her.

1221
01:18:11,400 --> 01:18:14,361
She has confessed
that she is guilty

1222
01:18:14,403 --> 01:18:16,321
of participating
in these crimes

1223
01:18:16,363 --> 01:18:19,616
so that she would be guilty of the crime
of murder, yes.

1224
01:18:21,535 --> 01:18:23,745
Throughout the morning,
friends and relatives arrived

1225
01:18:23,787 --> 01:18:25,247
at the Reade family home to pay...

1226
01:18:25,289 --> 01:18:28,417
I'm so sorry.

1227
01:18:28,458 --> 01:18:30,794
This is all my fault.

1228
01:18:30,836 --> 01:18:33,922
If I hadn't read
her letters

1229
01:18:33,964 --> 01:18:36,925
and insisted
on meeting her...

1230
01:18:36,967 --> 01:18:41,680
because you'd already
decided to let her go.

1231
01:18:41,722 --> 01:18:45,434
As the cortege made its way through
the Courtland area of Manchester,

1232
01:18:45,434 --> 01:18:48,604
neighbors stood silently
in memory of Pauline.

1233
01:18:48,645 --> 01:18:52,232
Later, her body was interred
at a nearby cemetery.

1234
01:18:53,901 --> 01:18:56,069
More than two decades
after her death,

1235
01:18:56,111 --> 01:18:59,781
the family were at last able
to lay their daughter to rest.

1236
01:19:02,117 --> 01:19:05,579
I'll call the police.
Get rid of the photographers.

1237
01:19:05,621 --> 01:19:08,373
At graveside, the mother
of Lesley Ann Downey,

1238
01:19:08,415 --> 01:19:10,542
yet another child
murdered on the moors.

1239
01:19:10,584 --> 01:19:13,462
For Pauline Reade,
the last chapter

1240
01:19:13,504 --> 01:19:15,589
of her tragic life has been written.

1241
01:19:15,631 --> 01:19:18,467
John Draper,
ITN, Manchester.

1242
01:19:34,483 --> 01:19:38,195
Forgive me, Father,
for I have sinned.

1243
01:19:38,237 --> 01:19:40,489
It has been some weeks
since my last confession,

1244
01:19:40,489 --> 01:19:43,742
during which time
much has changed.

1245
01:19:45,202 --> 01:19:49,498
My actions have
hurt my family...

1246
01:19:49,540 --> 01:19:53,210
my friends, and not to mention
the families of the victims.

1247
01:19:56,964 --> 01:20:00,926
Now I ask God

1248
01:20:00,968 --> 01:20:03,303
for His guidance,

1249
01:20:03,345 --> 01:20:07,683
His strength,

1250
01:20:07,683 --> 01:20:10,644
and above all
His compassion.

1251
01:20:13,272 --> 01:20:16,275
For in His perfection,

1252
01:20:16,316 --> 01:20:19,695
he forgives all
His creatures.

1253
01:20:22,531 --> 01:20:25,784
I beseech you, Lord,

1254
01:20:25,826 --> 01:20:29,121
forgive me.

1255
01:20:31,582 --> 01:20:34,501
And give me strength

1256
01:20:34,543 --> 01:20:39,256
to follow your
immaculate example...

1257
01:20:41,258 --> 01:20:44,928
so that I might put aside
my personal hurt...

1258
01:20:50,058 --> 01:20:52,895
and forgive this woman.

1259
01:21:33,185 --> 01:21:36,813
Shh.

1260
01:21:36,855 --> 01:21:39,149
Go on, sit.

1261
01:21:39,191 --> 01:21:43,612
You're all right.
Shh.

1262
01:21:43,654 --> 01:21:45,280
Shh.

1263
01:21:45,322 --> 01:21:47,324
What's the matter
with you?

1264
01:21:47,366 --> 01:21:49,910
Gonna get real fucking angry
if you don't hurry up.

1265
01:21:49,952 --> 01:21:51,495
What's that look for?

1266
01:21:51,537 --> 01:21:53,205
If you don't shush,

1267
01:21:53,247 --> 01:21:56,458
I'll have to shut
your mouth for you.

1268
01:21:56,458 --> 01:21:58,627
And I'll forget myself,

1269
01:21:58,669 --> 01:22:02,130
and I'll hit you
once more.

1270
01:22:02,130 --> 01:22:05,342
Will you stop it?

1271
01:22:05,384 --> 01:22:08,470
Stop it.
Stop it.

1272
01:22:41,628 --> 01:22:44,965
So many questions to ask you,
such a long and distinguished career,

1273
01:22:45,007 --> 01:22:46,675
but I'm gonna start
with the book.

1274
01:22:46,717 --> 01:22:48,385
What prompted you
to write it?

1275
01:22:48,427 --> 01:22:50,679
As a lifelong Christian
and scholar,

1276
01:22:50,721 --> 01:22:54,516
I've always been interested
in ideas of sanctity.

1277
01:22:54,558 --> 01:22:57,561
But more than that,
I think it was probably

1278
01:22:57,603 --> 01:23:01,398
the entirely selfish desire
to spend a little time with my heroes.

1279
01:23:01,440 --> 01:23:03,192
Do you have a favorite?

1280
01:23:03,192 --> 01:23:05,569
A favorite?
Hey, what a question.

1281
01:23:05,611 --> 01:23:10,365
I commend you for distilling
so succinctly such a complex subject.

1282
01:23:10,407 --> 01:23:13,785
Hey, Myra, I think your
Frankie boy is on the radio.

1283
01:23:13,827 --> 01:23:16,038
- Lord Porn.
- Dismas of Calvary,

1284
01:23:16,079 --> 01:23:17,915
the thief crucified
next to Jesus.

1285
01:23:17,956 --> 01:23:21,919
I've always been drawn
to outcasts

1286
01:23:21,960 --> 01:23:24,922
and people on
the fringes of society.

1287
01:23:24,963 --> 01:23:28,050
And St. Dismas,
having spent most of his life

1288
01:23:28,091 --> 01:23:29,718
as a violent criminal,

1289
01:23:29,760 --> 01:23:34,056
the miracle of his repentance
at the end on the cross...

1290
01:23:34,097 --> 01:23:36,767
Yes, I think he would
have to have my vote.

1291
01:23:36,808 --> 01:23:38,435
Interesting.

1292
01:23:38,477 --> 01:23:41,730
The time is coming up
to 20 past 2:00.

1293
01:23:41,772 --> 01:23:43,649
We're gonna take
some calls.

1294
01:23:43,690 --> 01:23:46,735
David, what's your
question about the saints?

1295
01:23:46,777 --> 01:23:48,862
I want to know how
your esteemed guest

1296
01:23:48,904 --> 01:23:50,822
can look himself in
the mirror each morning.

1297
01:23:50,864 --> 01:23:53,575
I'm assuming this is
a question about Myra Hindley.

1298
01:23:53,617 --> 01:23:56,453
How could you rub salt
in the wounds of the families like that,

1299
01:23:56,495 --> 01:23:58,247
campaigning on behalf
of that monster?

1300
01:23:58,288 --> 01:24:00,415
I certainly take exception
to that description,

1301
01:24:00,457 --> 01:24:02,751
but I made it quite clear
before coming on this program

1302
01:24:02,793 --> 01:24:05,629
that I would not be answering questions
about Ms. Hindley today.

1303
01:24:05,671 --> 01:24:09,758
Of course. Next caller is Judy
who's in Sheppey.

1304
01:24:09,800 --> 01:24:12,094
My call is also
about Ms. Hindley.

1305
01:24:12,135 --> 01:24:14,763
In view of everything
we now know about it,

1306
01:24:14,805 --> 01:24:17,391
don't you regret having
supported her all that time?

1307
01:24:17,432 --> 01:24:21,019
Once again, madam, I'm afraid I must
decline to answer questions about her.

1308
01:24:21,061 --> 01:24:23,981
It's a simple answer,
Lord Longford... yes or no.

1309
01:24:24,022 --> 01:24:26,817
Do you regret it?

1310
01:24:36,785 --> 01:24:38,829
Not at all.

1311
01:24:38,871 --> 01:24:40,122
As a matter of fact,

1312
01:24:40,122 --> 01:24:42,958
I consider my visiting
Myra Hindley,

1313
01:24:42,958 --> 01:24:45,586
and indeed all
the other prisoners

1314
01:24:45,627 --> 01:24:47,880
I visited
for over 50 years,

1315
01:24:47,921 --> 01:24:49,923
to be one of the great
blessings of my life.

1316
01:24:49,965 --> 01:24:52,801
Now perhaps we could
get back to the subject of saints.

1317
01:24:52,843 --> 01:24:54,303
Well, hasn't she
betrayed you?

1318
01:24:54,344 --> 01:24:56,138
She's ruined
your good name.

1319
01:24:56,180 --> 01:24:58,348
She's taken all of
the hard work you did for her

1320
01:24:58,390 --> 01:25:00,142
and thrown it
back in your face.

1321
01:25:02,227 --> 01:25:04,813
Um... yes.

1322
01:25:04,855 --> 01:25:07,900
Perhaps there's some
truth in that.

1323
01:25:10,110 --> 01:25:12,070
Forgiving her
has proven difficult,

1324
01:25:12,112 --> 01:25:13,822
very difficult.

1325
01:25:13,864 --> 01:25:15,657
Not for what
she's done to me...

1326
01:25:15,699 --> 01:25:17,659
that's neither here
nor there...

1327
01:25:17,659 --> 01:25:21,538
but for the terrible
crimes themselves.

1328
01:25:23,498 --> 01:25:28,128
Forgiveness is the very
cornerstone of my faith.

1329
01:25:28,170 --> 01:25:31,840
And the struggle
to deepen my faith

1330
01:25:31,882 --> 01:25:36,136
is my life's journey.

1331
01:25:36,178 --> 01:25:38,805
In that respect,

1332
01:25:38,847 --> 01:25:43,352
she has enriched
my spiritual life beyond measure,

1333
01:25:43,393 --> 01:25:46,688
and for that I will always
be grateful to her.

1334
01:25:52,945 --> 01:25:57,199
If people think that
makes me weak or mad,

1335
01:25:57,199 --> 01:25:59,034
so be it.

1336
01:25:59,034 --> 01:26:01,745
That is the path
I am committed to...

1337
01:26:04,206 --> 01:26:08,210
To love the sinner
but hate the sins...

1338
01:26:10,921 --> 01:26:13,924
To assume the best in people
and not the worst...

1339
01:26:15,592 --> 01:26:19,888
To believe that anyone,
no matter how evil,

1340
01:26:19,930 --> 01:26:23,559
can be redeemed,

1341
01:26:23,600 --> 01:26:26,395
eventually.

1342
01:26:29,940 --> 01:26:33,902
Right. The time is
coming up to 2:20.

1343
01:26:33,944 --> 01:26:36,738
Lord Longford is with us
for the next couple of hours.

1344
01:26:36,738 --> 01:26:40,576
And our switchboard looks
like it's about to explode.

1345
01:26:40,576 --> 01:26:43,370
Next caller,
Lionel in Seven Oaks.

1346
01:26:52,588 --> 01:26:55,215
Look at you!

1347
01:26:55,257 --> 01:26:58,927
Which prison were
you at today?

1348
01:26:58,969 --> 01:27:02,514
Carlisle.

1349
01:27:04,183 --> 01:27:07,311
The train was delayed
coming back, I'm afraid.

1350
01:27:07,352 --> 01:27:08,937
Snow on the tracks.

1351
01:27:08,979 --> 01:27:10,397
Carlisle.

1352
01:27:10,439 --> 01:27:13,775
You must be mad.
You're too old for this.

1353
01:27:13,775 --> 01:27:16,445
I'm going to get rid
of all the requests

1354
01:27:16,486 --> 01:27:18,572
that aren't
local from now on.

1355
01:27:18,614 --> 01:27:22,951
- Oh, look.
- What?

1356
01:27:22,993 --> 01:27:26,538
This one's from Myra.

1357
01:27:42,179 --> 01:27:43,889
Hello, Frank.

1358
01:27:43,931 --> 01:27:45,140
Oh, there you are.

1359
01:27:45,182 --> 01:27:48,143
Hello.

1360
01:27:48,185 --> 01:27:52,648
Goodness.
How well you look.

1361
01:27:52,648 --> 01:27:55,692
Rubbish.

1362
01:27:55,734 --> 01:27:57,736
My hair is falling out

1363
01:27:57,778 --> 01:28:00,030
and I'm dying
of emphysema.

1364
01:28:00,072 --> 01:28:03,992
Well, you still look
wonderful to me.

1365
01:28:04,034 --> 01:28:05,994
Well, you're blind.

1366
01:28:06,036 --> 01:28:08,747
Nearly, yes.

1367
01:28:11,041 --> 01:28:15,045
Frank, the reason why I've
asked to see you today...

1368
01:28:16,588 --> 01:28:19,925
I made up my mind
that if there was one thing

1369
01:28:19,967 --> 01:28:23,595
I was going to do
before it was too late,

1370
01:28:23,637 --> 01:28:27,933
it would be to apologize
to you in person.

1371
01:28:29,393 --> 01:28:33,272
Those are terrible
things I did to you...

1372
01:28:36,859 --> 01:28:39,611
Lying to you like that.

1373
01:28:39,653 --> 01:28:42,322
I'm sorry.

1374
01:28:55,002 --> 01:28:58,547
I couldn't tell you
everything, Frank.

1375
01:29:02,092 --> 01:29:05,554
In prison, you never
tell anyone everything.

1376
01:29:10,100 --> 01:29:13,770
And your full
confession before God...

1377
01:29:16,106 --> 01:29:19,067
Was that a lie too?

1378
01:29:19,109 --> 01:29:22,070
I'm trying, Frank.

1379
01:29:22,112 --> 01:29:25,824
I'm really trying to know
the God that you know.

1380
01:29:28,410 --> 01:29:32,331
But if you'd been
there that night

1381
01:29:32,372 --> 01:29:36,376
on the moors
in the moonlight

1382
01:29:36,418 --> 01:29:41,089
when we did the first one,

1383
01:29:41,131 --> 01:29:44,760
then you'd know that evil

1384
01:29:44,801 --> 01:29:47,763
can be a spiritual
experience too.

1385
01:29:59,358 --> 01:30:01,652
You know we only missed it
by a few weeks.

1386
01:30:03,028 --> 01:30:06,782
- What?
- The death sentence.

1387
01:30:08,158 --> 01:30:10,494
They abolished it while
we were still on remand.

1388
01:30:10,536 --> 01:30:12,829
Looking back, don't you think
it would have been

1389
01:30:12,871 --> 01:30:14,915
better for everyone
if they'd just hung us?

1390
01:30:14,957 --> 01:30:17,501
Certainly not.

1391
01:30:17,543 --> 01:30:20,629
Only God has the right
to take human life.

1392
01:30:20,671 --> 01:30:23,882
Would he have not wanted to give
the families that comfort?

1393
01:30:25,217 --> 01:30:27,386
None of us knows
the true purpose

1394
01:30:27,427 --> 01:30:29,888
of our lives on Earth.

1395
01:30:29,930 --> 01:30:32,808
Besides...

1396
01:30:32,808 --> 01:30:35,310
had you been hanged,
I would never have had

1397
01:30:35,310 --> 01:30:38,272
the privilege
of getting to know you.

1398
01:30:43,193 --> 01:30:46,196
You really believe that,
don't you?

1399
01:30:56,832 --> 01:30:59,459
It must be rather
a nice place to be.

1400
01:30:59,501 --> 01:31:01,170
Where?

1401
01:31:01,211 --> 01:31:03,755
Inside your head.

1402
01:31:03,797 --> 01:31:08,635
Oh, I'm not so sure
about that.

1403
01:31:13,473 --> 01:31:16,393
A fine pair we are then.

1404
01:31:16,435 --> 01:31:18,937
Yes.

